headline: Netflix & TSMC earnings, retail sales, Fed talk: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton breaks down the biggest stories to watch on Thursday, July 17. More earnings are coming. In the morning, Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company (TSM), GE Aerospace (GE), Novartis (NVS), Abbott Laboratories (ABT), and Pepsico (PEP) are reporting earnings. Netflix (NFLX) will announce its results in the afternoon. US retail sales data for June is coming out in the morning, with economists expecting a rebound. More commentary from several Federal Reserve officials is on its way, with remarks expected from Fed governor Adriana Kugler, San Francisco Fed President Mary Daly, Fed governor Lisa Cook, and Fed governor Christopher Waller. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here.
